About Nine Lanterns

Nine Lanterns &lt; http://www.ninelanterns.com.au/ &gt; is a fun and funky company
specialising in eLearning and online community projects for a range of
blue-chip companies as well as education and not-for-profit organisations.

We are one of Australia's leading eLearning companies, with a head office in
Melbourne, Australia.

We are looking for a range of talented staff to join us in our newly
established Shanghai office to work on some fantastic projects.
Position Description: PHP Web Developer - Shanghai

We need someone with a thorough understanding of PHP application
development, preferably with experience using the
Drupal&lt; http://www.drupal.org/ &gt;framework. You will be part of a vibrant
and highly skilled team comprising
project managers, developers, illustrators, graphic and instructional
designers working from both our Melbourne and Shanghai offices. Daily tasks
will include writing and testing well documented PHP code inside Drupal
modules or snippets, constructing tests using Selenium, deploying code to
test and staging servers and maintaining up to date work status in our
bugtracking system. You will report to a Project Manager/SCRUM Master on
projects, and be supported by a Technical Lead in the Melbourne office. We
are using SCRUM to develop our web projects, with an emphasis on creating
working code with tests over heavy up front documentation, so the work
involves regular communication with other team members. You will not be
asked about your TPS Reports.
Skills:

Essential:

- PHP
- HTML/CSS
- SQL
- Attention to detail, rigorous testing during development, writing
clean code
- Ability to learn new skills
- Experience with version control systems (SVN, CVS)
- Reasonable command of English

Nice to have:

- Computer Science / Software Engineering degree
- Drupal experience
- Experience with testing frameworks (Selenium)
- Javascript/AJAX/etc
- Linux web server administration
- Flash (ActionScript 2.0)
- XML/XSLT
- Experience contributing to Open-Source projects

Remuneration

- Competitive, commensurate with experience, with Share Options on
offer for great candidates.

To Apply

Please email chinaj ... @ninelanterns.com.au, with the subject
'2007-Oct-Web-Developer'. Include your CV and any related experiences. Or
call +86 159 2167 6061 to chat with Mike Hall. Interviews will be conducted
immediately and there will be a short PHP test during the interview.

This ad also viewable at
http://www.ninelanterns.com.au/careers/current-openings/php-web-devel...

Looking forward to hearing from you!
